<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7380] Native protocol needs keepalive, we should add it</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7380</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On clients connecting to C* 1.2.15 using native protocol. We see that when the client is bounced, the old connection is not going away&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On Thrift, there is the rpc_keepalive but there is no similar feature for the native protocol&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Cassandra 1.2, 2.0&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12720610">CASSANDRA-7380</key>
            <summary>Native protocol needs keepalive, we should add it</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
