                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14028089" author="kohlisankalp" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 17:45:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should definitely add this. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028257" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 19:20:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reusing the rpc_keepalive option should be fine, since I can&apos;t imagine we need thrift/native granularity here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028600" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 23:52:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patches against 1.2 and 2.0 to reuse rpc_keepalive for the native proto.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028654" author="kohlisankalp" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 00:34:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looks good. There is SimpleClient.java which also sets some options like this. Don&apos;t know what it is used for. &lt;br/&gt;
Also the patch will be different for trunk as options are set in Server.java&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028672" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 00:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SimpleClient is for stress, so I didn&apos;t bother since keepalive there shouldn&apos;t be needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028821" author="kohlisankalp" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 04:50:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the patch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14029218" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 14:48:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
